subSection.paragraph:
The genus
Ctenorillo Verhoeff, 1942
is distributed across Africa and South America (
Taiti et al. 1998
; Schmalfuss 2003 ;
Boyko et al. 2008
;
Campos-Filho et al. 2014
, 2017 ; Cifuentes & Da Silva 2023 ;
Carpio-Díaz et al. 2023
). In Brazil , three species are known:
C. mineri ( Van Name, 1936 )
from Brazil , Guyana and Venezuela ;
C. ferrarai Campos-Filho, Araujo & Taiti, 2014
from Brazil ; and
C. tuberosus (BuddeLund, 1904)
from Brazil , Haiti and Germany (introduced) (
Campos-Filho et al. 2018
).

